{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885144440,"sessionID":"ses_284ff6e93ffeV1WxMMqeg8pblM","part":{"id":"prt_d7b00d14b001GrT8tJxTSNDLGF","messageID":"msg_d7b00c6850017KyX7OCzrk159D","sessionID":"ses_284ff6e93ffeV1WxMMqeg8pblM","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-f5bed9d540084286860124de4965595e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-033/CHANGE.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-033/CHANGE.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-033 — Makefile 构建目标体系\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: - **AR**: AR-033\n5: - **Title**: Makefile 构建目标体系\n6: - **Module**: root\n7: - **Language**: Makefile\n8: - **Size**: M\n9: - **Status**: Completed\n10: \n11: ## Description\n12: \n13: Makefile 构建目标体系，用于统一管理项目的构建、测试、清理等操作。\n14: \n15: ## Dependencies\n16: \n17: - Go toolchain 1.25+\n18: - Python 3.10+\n19: - Docker 20.10+ (for container builds)\n20: - GNU Make 4.0+\n21: \n22: ## Related Changes\n23: \n24: None\n25: \n26: ## Implementation Notes\n27: \n28: ### Files Created\n29: \n30: #### Core Files\n31: - **Makefile** - Root Makefile with all main targets and variables\n32: - **VERSION** - Version file for tracking project version (0.1.0)\n33: - **.gitignore** - Updated gitignore to exclude build artifacts\n34: \n35: #### Sub-Makefiles (.makefiles/)\n36: - **go.mk** - Go-specific build, test, and dependency management targets\n37: - **python.mk** - Python-specific build, test, and dependency management targets\n38: - **docker.mk** - Docker image build and management targets\n39: - **test.mk** - Test execution and coverage reporting targets\n40: - **lint.mk** - Code quality, formatting, and linting targets\n41: - **clean.mk** - Build artifact cleanup targets\n42: - **deps.mk** - Dependency management targets\n43: - **release.mk** - Release creation and packaging targets\n44: - **utils.mk** - Utility targets (info, check, CI, dev)\n45: - **docs.mk** - Documentation generation targets\n46: \n47: #### Build Scripts (scripts/)\n48: - **build.sh** - Build script for all components\n49: - **test.sh** - Test execution script\n50: - **release.sh** - Release creation script\n51: \n52: #### Directories Created\n53: - **bin/** - Build artifacts directory (in .gitignore)\n54: - **dist/** - Distribution packages directory (in .gitignore)\n55: - **coverage/** - Test coverage reports directory (in .gitignore)\n56: - **reports/** - Test reports directory (in .gitignore)\n57: - **.makefiles/** - Sub-Makefiles directory\n58: - **scripts/** - Build scripts directory\n59: \n60: ### Build Targets Summary\n61: \n62: #### Build Targets\n63: - `build` - Build all Go and Python components\n64: - `build-go` - Build all Go binaries\n65: - `build-python` - Build Python packages (wheel and sdist)\n66: - `build-agentd` - Build agentd binary\n67: - `build-picod` - Build picod binary\n68: - `build-agentcube` - Build agentcube CLI binary\n69: - `build-agentcube-util` - Build agentcube-util binary\n70: - `build-code-interpreter` - Build code-interpreter binary\n71: - `build-agent-runtime` - Build agent-runtime binary\n72: \n73: #### Test Targets\n74: - `test` - Run all tests (Go and Python)\n75: - `test-go` - Run all Go tests\n76: - `test-python` - Run all Python tests\n77: - `test-go-cover` - Generate Go test coverage report\n78: - `test-python-cover` - Generate Python test coverage report\n79: - `test-integration` - Run all integration tests\n80: - `test-e2e` - Run end-to-end tests\n81: \n82: #### Lint Targets\n83: - `lint` - Run all linting checks\n84: - `lint-go` - Run Go linting (gofmt, go vet, golangci-lint)\n85: - `lint-python` - Run Python linting (ruff, mypy, flake8)\n86: - `format` - Format all code\n87: - `format-go` - Format Go code (gofmt, goimports)\n88: - `format-python` - Format Python code (black, isort)\n89: \n90: #### Docker Targets\n91: - `docker-build` - Build all Docker images\n92: - `docker-build-agentd` - Build agentd Docker image\n93: - `docker-build-picod` - Build picod Docker image\n94: - `docker-build-agentcube` - Build agentcube Docker image\n95: - `docker-push` - Push all Docker images to registry\n96: \n97: #### Clean Targets\n98: - `clean` - Clean all build artifacts\n99: - `clean-go` - Clean Go build artifacts\n100: - `clean-python` - Clean Python build artifacts\n101: - `clean-all` - Clean all artifacts including reports\n102: \n103: #### Dependency Targets\n104: - `deps` - Download all dependencies\n105: - `deps-go` - Download Go dependencies\n106: - `deps-python` - Download Python dependencies\n107: - `deps-update` - Update all dependencies\n108: \n109: #### Release Targets\n110: - `release` - Create release build\n111: - `release-all` - Complete release process\n112: - `tag` - Create git tag for current version\n113: - `snapshot` - Create snapshot build\n114: \n115: #### Development Targets\n116: - `dev-setup` - Set up development environment\n117: - `dev-up` - Start development services\n118: - `dev-down` - Stop development services\n119: \n120: #### CI/CD Targets\n121: - `ci` - Run CI pipeline\n122: - `ci-build` - CI: Build all components\n123: - `ci-test` - CI: Run all tests\n124: - `ci-lint` - CI: Run all linting checks\n125: \n126: #### Utility Targets\n127: - `help` - Show help message\n128: - `version` - Display version information\n129: - `vars` - Display all Makefile variables\n130: - `info` - Display build information\n131: - `check-tools` - Check if required tools are installed\n132: \n133: ### Usage Examples\n134: \n135: ```bash\n136: # Show help\n137: make help\n138: \n139: # Build everything\n140: make build\n141: \n142: # Run all tests\n143: make test\n144: \n145: # Run linting\n146: make lint\n147: \n148: # Format code\n149: make format\n150: \n151: # Clean build artifacts\n152: make clean\n153: \n154: # Build in release mode\n155: BUILD_MODE=release make build\n156: \n157: # Create release\n158: make release-all\n159: ```\n160: \n161: ### Key Features\n162: \n163: 1. **Unified Interface** - Single entry point for all build operations\n164: 2. **Multi-language Support** - Go and Python build targets\n165: 3. **Cross-platform Builds** - Support for linux/amd64, linux/arm64, darwin/amd64, darwin/arm64\n166: 4. **Color-coded Output** - Improved readability with color-coded messages\n167: 5. **Comprehensive Help** - Self-documenting with `make help`\n168: 6. **CI/CD Friendly** - Targets designed for automated pipelines\n169: 7. **Development Mode** - Race detection and debug symbols by default\n170: 8. **Release Mode** - Optimized builds with stripped binaries\n171: 9. **Test Coverage** - Coverage reports for both Go and Python\n172: 10. **Docker Integration** - Build and push Docker images\n173: \n174: ### Test Coverage\n175: \n176: All Makefile targets have been designed and tested to ensure:\n177: - Targets execute successfully\n178: - Error messages are clear and helpful\n179: - Dependencies are properly managed\n180: - Build artifacts are placed in correct locations\n181: \n182: ## Deferred Items\n183: \n184: None\n\n(End of file - total 184 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-033 — Makefile 构建目标体系\n\n## Metadata\n- **AR**: AR-033\n- **Title**: Makefile 构建目标体系\n- **Module**: root\n- **Language**: Makefile\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: Completed\n\n## Description\n\nMakefile 构建目标体系，用于统一管理项目的构建、测试、清理等操作。\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Go toolchain 1.25+\n- Python 3.10+\n- Docker 20.10+ (for container builds)\n- GNU Make 4.0+","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-033/CHANGE.md","time":{"start":1775885144423,"end":1775885144438}}}}
